05/09/2004
ZAGREB, Croatia -- Croatia's government said Friday (3 September) that it would appoint a chief negotiator with the EU next week.
Cabinet spokesman Ratko Macek also said the government would make an all-out effort to launch negotiations with Brussels by March 2005.
He added that the entire EU negotiations team would be in place by October.
(HINA, HIC - 03/09/04)
